metadata.name: Chimalmat Relics #76
metadata.description:
'Chimalmat Relics' is a generative art project that pays homage to the great American civilizations (such as the Aztecs, the Mayans and the Incas).

Each piece of the project has 4 stages. 

The first is the expansion, the flourishing, the formation of the cities. In this stage each work begins to grow. The lines evoke the complexity of the cultures and how they progressed, occupying more land, becoming more intricate, complex, beautiful and elaborate. The circles represent the individuals of these cultures, they are large because they represent the greatness of these individuals. The squares represent the temples, so important to these societies.

The next stage is maturation, it is when lines begin to appear in the background that cover the entire piece and represent the acquired knowledge and wisdom of these cultures, their knowledge of nature, the stars, their art.

The third stage is decadence, we already know what happened to these civilizations, so this stage enters like a wave from the left that sweeps everything away, erases and blurs the work, the history. It represents the conquest.

The last stage represents history, memory, what survives today, what we can reconstruct, infer, yearn for those times, there is much that was lost, but the essence remains, it is still there. It allows us and obliges us in a certain way to contemplate and appreciate it.

-----

Press 'e' to export a PNG

-----

Artwork by @cristianrohr 2022.

Made with P5js and <3.

metadata.name: Impressions of Order #255
metadata.description:
‘Impressions of Order’ is a collection of 300 generative compositions. 

Inspired by 90s ROM cartridges, server farms and future cityscapes this project explores perception and documentation of ‘order’ within complex systems. 

--------------------------------------------------------

This artwork is best enjoyed in high-resolution so that the subtle layering, colour shifts, variation in hard and soft edges, faint impressions of construction, and the various low-probability glitchy events can be fully appreciated. 

By default, the artwork will load in 2K resolution (1400 x 2000 px). It is recommended that you view the work in 4K or 6K to appreciate the finer details. 

The keyboard buttons: “2”, “4”, and “6” can be pressed to change the resolution to 2K, 4K and 6K resolution accordingly. 

To download an image at its current resolution, press the keyboard button “S”.

--------------------------------------------------------

Artwork created with p5.js

@nbswwit
Sept 2022

metadata.name: Garden Of Symmetry #245
metadata.description:
Sometimes, things look better when seen from the distance. Not from far away, but from a length that allows one to see what’s possibly underneath. Or, you may not see anything. Instead, you can just enjoy things falling into place.

Get a pack of shattered glass, snow, or ice*, uncovering a pattern. Or an axis of dancing geometries. Enter the Garden of Symmetry.

The graphic is a plottable SVG file in A3 format, ready to be drawn using a pen plotter. In the full screen view, click somewhere on the artwork to download a copy.

I recommend to optimize the SVG before plotting, i.e. using vpype. I also recommend to draw the graphic using 0.7mm pen.

License: CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/ - @jakub_antolak

———
*choose your option

metadata.name: Unstable Anticipation #66
metadata.description:
Minimal poster prints of blocks in motion.

Varying block arrangements fall from the canvas's top and interact with pegs near the bottom. After the animation completes, the scene is redrawn with a halftone pattern.

Matter JS is used to calculate the physics.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 2318x3000px

Features
* The length of the simulation
* Number, size, and position of the pegs
* Halftone grid size
* Varying amount of roughness for distorted halftone shapes
* Shape arrangement and composition
* 60/40% Color or monochrome

Copyright (c) 2022 Matt Perkins, hello@mattperkins.me, @nudoru on Twitter. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: Nature Force #46
metadata.description:
Nature forces
It is the expression of mother nature in static and textured forms.

Central piece represent the sun radiation, the sea stregth and the atoms complexity.
This piece manifests in 3 pieces, swirl, radiant and atom. Compose of 22 layers, that 
follow golden ratio 1,1618. All 3 have 75% chance to appear !

Canvas is composed of 3 diffents effects, first Wind force showing their blades, 
second Mandala represent plants symmetry demonstrated in various manifestations in nature 
and last one Liquify bringing the sea movements and their inclusion of other elements in them.

Finally, the picture involves all this power, keeping the centerpiece highlighted, 
but it still has its representativeness. 
Bringing in the first point, Thunder, the electrical forces to compose,
 in second, the union of two elements becoming the Booger density and 
finally bringing the technology to the context that everything is part of the 
nature, formation of pixel.

Nature sounds can change between sign wind, waterfalls and thunder rain.

You have 1% chance to mint nature power, 
this feature means movement to your piece, can be 0.00 or 100.00.

You have 1,5% chance to mint 3x feature simple, on piece, canvas and picture. 
Simple means no piece, clear canvas and picture, but if have that lucky, 
next drop will be free.


Press 'S' to print in full screen view and full quality '4k'. 

Features : 
Nature Life Power have 1% chance to be on.
Central piece, swirl,atom and radiant have 75% chance to appear.
Full Simple 1,5% chance to combine.(Simple + Simple + Simple)
Full Storm 0,4% chance to combine. (Atom + Thunder + Mandala + Thunder rain)
Full Water 0,4% chance to combine.( Swirl + Liquify + Booger + Waterfalls)
Full Tornado 0,4% chance to combine.(Radiant + Wind + Pixel + Sign wind)

metadata.name: In Due Time #56
metadata.description:
“In Due Time” is a collaborative generative collection between artists Melissa Wiederrecht and Amber Vittoria. Inspired by Wiederrecht’s mastery of line and Vittoria’s notable palette, this 1/1/250 series captures the present moment. It serves as a reminder that we are more similar than we are different, leveraging homogeneous shapes to create distinctive compositions.

Vittoria’s poem for the collection:

“In Due Time”
We will all become
Particles dancing
Across the skyline.

The artwork listed is indeed authentic, created by, and copyright to artists Melissa Wiederrecht and Amber Vittoria; the purchase of this NFT is a purchase of the asset, not of the copyright.

-------------------------------------------

To save a high-resolution image for printing, click “open” under the image on the page for your token, and then hit:

Digits “1” through “9” to get an image that is 1000 through 9000px tall.  This may take a while, depending on the size and your computer, so please be patient.

metadata.name: This is not a Branch #89
metadata.description:
The title of the work is a paraphrase of René Magritte's famous work. In today's world, the irony embedded in it is wrapped up in a new way. How can we tell one from the other, such as natural from natural, if they look the same or perform the same functions?
I was inspired to create branches by the news of the development of mechanical trees that can capture carbon dioxide from the atmosphere. These cyborgs are able to do the job much more efficiently than their natural counterparts. Soon there will be an entire forest of mechanical plants in Arizona.
The mechanical trunks are tall columns, 1.5 metres in diameter, which are made up of discs, just like the stem of the mechanical-digital branch in this work. It is capable of twisting and taking a variety of forms, from entirely natural to more angular, industrial, mechanistic ones. Where does the fine line between our recognition of a living organism and an artificial one pass, does it exist and will it be important to us in the future?

The palettes are taken from Japanese prints celebrating the beauty of nature.
Plus there is a vaporwave palette that reminds me of the game Metal Mutant, the aesthetics of which I was fascinated with as a child.

Made with p5.js code
To save the image, press the 's' key. Enjoy!

September, 2022
Julia V & YulikolaY

metadata.name: Acid Warning #89
metadata.description:
Acid Warning is an algorithm that generates LSD warning labels.  When Bear and his students were setting up their Richmond acid lab they commissioned this series of warning label designs for their equipment.

The artwork was abandoned as the chemists quickly found it impossible to avoid getting high while working in the lab. Instead of labeling their laboratory gear, they all embraced the “Acid Makers’ Queasy” for weeks on end.  This generative psychedelia project is a reprint of the Bear’s lost Acid Warning series.    

- Double click to enable turntable mode
- Click and drag and zoom to move around in 3D
- Don’t take too much acid in real life homies!

Created by @capnganj - one love <3

metadata.name: Calmer waters - reissue #4
metadata.description:
This is a reissue of project #10669
https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/10669

I long for calmer waters. This piece is about that. It's a counterpoint. It reflects some of my best memories of the sea: the warm salty air on my face, interspersed with a cool breeze, leaving my lips salty tasting. The gentle rushing of the water. 

The sea with its vast panorama's can make you feel insignificant in the grand scheme of things. But this piece is about hope.
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
About this reissue: An update of the security policy of fx(hash) blocks external scripts. This update stops malicious actors; they could try to interact with a user’s wallet. So, this update is really a good thing. It’s a safeguard. However, due to this update the original project no longer loads in live view and after consultation and deliberation I decided to reissue the token without the use of external scripts (p5js). 

Only holders of the original project are on the allow list. 

Royalties are for the minter.

metadata.name: La Veranada #52
metadata.description:
My mother lives in the countryside with her husband and her work is the breeding and grazing of goats, cows and horses. They live a cyclical life marked by two big stages during their livestock year: "La Veranada" and "La Invernada".
The "invernada" is the place where they live during what we could call the long winter, that is, from April to November. "La Invernada" is below, in the plains, in the pampas, in accessible places, where it is easy to supply the animals with fodder.
"La Veranada" is the place where they go during the long summer, from November to April, it is above, in the mountain ranges, on the heights, where the summer pastures abound, where they go for months to take care, alone, of the goats, cows and calves.
The transfer of the animals to the summer pasture is called "Arreo", my mother's husband guides the animals on his horse. The "Arreo" lasts about 5 days.
In both places they live in what they call "el puesto". "El puesto" is their home.
In "La veranada", "El puesto" is simple. A common living room, with a wood stove, a table, some chairs and shelves to store flour, *"mate" and salt. A small bedroom replenishes the strength worn out by the daily work. Water for drinking, cooking and washing is drawn from a nearby stream.
Work is abundant. As a common element, both in winter and summer, my mother's husband rides a horse daily and, accompanied by his dogs, goes to "watch" the cattle.
As a final point I wanted to thank you for taking your time and reading the story behind this project that I really enjoyed doing it, and on my tw profile you can read this story with real photos.

*Mate: is an Argentinean infusion, which is present all day long in the life of people who live in the countryside. It give you energy.

Press "S" in live mode to save image 2600 x 3000.
Please note that the algorithm can take some time to run.
Created by Fernando. NFT License 2.0.

metadata.name: Flustels #53
metadata.description:
Fully generative artwork in crayoning style.

The model uses Perlin noise map multiplied by map with flowers.
Each flower generated randomly with circles and ellipses. 

Each token is 100% unique.

Traits:
- 20 color palettes;
- 5 compositions;
- 9 background styles;
- 2 brush weights.

Press 's' to save .png with resolution 2000px * 2000px.

Renders fastest in Chrome browser.

Made with p5js, math and love by @ivposure

metadata.name: Irregular #42
metadata.description:
Irregular is a generative art project made to loop without an end.
Each iteration creates a random noise distributed grid of points. This base grid is the final static output image. Once created, it enters a deformation loop based on a flow movement, which is distorted and returns to the origin with a breathing rhythm.

Responsive, zoom out browser window and refresh to get a larger output.
's' save the current canvas

Made with love, javascript and p5js
2022 Diego Pintos, see LICENSE.md
